  <!-- Slide 8: How OmO works as one sophisticated plugin -->
  <Slide id="omo-plugin" variant="accent">
    <div class="content-slide omo-plugin">
      <p class="overline">Sophisticated Plugin Anatomy</p>
      <h2>One Plugin. <span class="highlight">Many Runtime Hooks.</span></h2>
      <p class="lead omo-plugin__lead">
        From OpenCode&rsquo;s view, OmO is just a plugin module that returns hooks.
        Inside, it composes config, tools, managers, lifecycle hooks, MCPs, and SDK calls into a harness layer.
      </p>

      <div class="omo-plugin__map" aria-label="How oh-my-openagent plugs into OpenCode hooks">
        <div class="omo-plugin__core" aria-label="OpenCode hooks object returned by OmO">
          <div class="omo-hooks-card__header">
            <span class="omo-plugin__core-kicker">returns</span>
            <span class="omo-plugin__core-title">hooks</span>
          </div>
          <div class="omo-hooks-object">
            <div class="omo-hooks-object__row"><code>config</code><span>shape runtime</span></div>
            <div class="omo-hooks-object__row"><code>tool</code><span>add tools</span></div>
            <div class="omo-hooks-object__row"><code>event</code><span>react to sessions</span></div>
            <div class="omo-hooks-object__row"><code>tool.execute.*</code><span>guard actions</span></div>
            <div class="omo-hooks-object__row"><code>experimental.*</code><span>preserve memory</span></div>
          </div>
          <span class="omo-plugin__core-sub">a plain object with enough extension points to become a harness</span>
        </div>

        <div class="omo-plugin__hooks-grid">
          <div class="omo-hook-card omo-hook-card--config">
            <span class="omo-hook-card__hook"><code>config</code></span>
            <h3>Shape the runtime</h3>
            <p>Agents, MCPs, commands, model defaults, runtime skill sources.</p>
            <pre class="omo-hook-card__code"><code>config.agent = omoAgents
config.mcp = builtinMcps</code></pre>
          </div>
          <div class="omo-hook-card omo-hook-card--tool">
            <span class="omo-hook-card__hook"><code>tool</code></span>
            <h3>Add capabilities</h3>
            <p>Background agents, task delegation, skill MCPs, team tools, hashline edit.</p>
            <pre class="omo-hook-card__code"><code>tool: &#123; task, skill_mcp,
        team_create &#125;</code></pre>
          </div>
          <div class="omo-hook-card omo-hook-card--before">
            <span class="omo-hook-card__hook"><code>tool.execute.before</code></span>
            <h3>Guard the action</h3>
            <p>Write guards, rule injection, comment checks, task routing, mode limits.</p>
            <pre class="omo-hook-card__code"><code>if (tool === "write")
  requireReadFirst(args)</code></pre>
          </div>
          <div class="omo-hook-card omo-hook-card--after">
            <span class="omo-hook-card__hook"><code>tool.execute.after</code></span>
            <h3>Clean up results</h3>
            <p>Output truncation, metadata recovery, read tagging, error recovery.</p>
            <pre class="omo-hook-card__code"><code>output.output = truncate(output)
output.metadata = recover()</code></pre>
          </div>
          <div class="omo-hook-card omo-hook-card--event">
            <span class="omo-hook-card__hook"><code>event</code></span>
            <h3>React to lifecycle</h3>
            <p>Idle wakeups, session errors, tmux sync, team mode, OpenClaw dispatch.</p>
            <pre class="omo-hook-card__code"><code>if (event.type === "session.idle")
  wakeParentSession()</code></pre>
          </div>
          <div class="omo-hook-card omo-hook-card--memory">
            <span class="omo-hook-card__hook"><code>experimental.*</code></span>
            <h3>Survive context walls</h3>
            <p>Message transforms, system transforms, compaction context, auto-continue.</p>
            <pre class="omo-hook-card__code"><code>output.context.push(savedTodos)
output.enabled = true</code></pre>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="omo-plugin__takeaway">
        <span>OpenCode exposes hooks.</span>
        <strong>OmO wires a harness through them.</strong>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Slide>

