  <!-- Slide 9.9: Where this is going — substantiated forward look -->
  <Slide id="future" variant="control">
    <div class="content-slide future">
      <p class="overline">Looking Ahead</p>
      <h2>Where This Is <span class="highlight">Going</span> <span class="future__caveat">(opinionated)</span></h2>
      <p class="lead future__lead">
        The action format is mostly settled. <strong>CodeAct</strong> &mdash; agents acting by writing and
        running code &mdash; beats rigid JSON tool-calls (<strong>up to 20% higher success rate</strong>)
        because code <em>composes</em>: loops, conditionals, piping one tool into the next.
        The next few years aren&rsquo;t a better action format. They&rsquo;re the
        three layers <em>around</em> it &mdash; the layers you just saw.
      </p>

      <!-- Orbital: a settled CodeAct core, three frontier layers orbiting it.
