  <!-- Slide 10: Key takeaways -->
  <Slide id="takeaways" variant="dark">
    <div class="content-slide takeaway-slide">
      <p class="overline">Wrapping Up</p>
      <h2>Key Takeaways</h2>
      <ol class="takeaway-list">
        <li>
          <strong>Code is the universal remote.</strong>
          An agent doesn&rsquo;t just write code &mdash; it <em>acts</em> through it. Paper briefs, issue triage,
          even judging another agent: same trick, different jobs.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>The harness is the product, not the model.</strong>
          Same engine, different opinions about context, tools, routing, and when to stop.
          That layer &mdash; OpenCode + OmO &mdash; is what you actually feel.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Token cost is a design surface.</strong>
          You can engineer it down (RTK), and there&rsquo;s a whole fast-moving field doing it.
          What reaches the model is a choice, not a given.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>The default is already a choice &mdash; so make it yours.</strong>
          Adopt &amp; reshape, or build up from primitives. Either way, own the harness
          instead of inheriting someone else&rsquo;s.
        </li>
      </ol>
      <div class="closing">
        <p class="closing__text">Don&rsquo;t just use an agent &mdash; <strong>own the harness around it.</strong></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Slide>

